12:05.880 --> 12:08.240
Just like I showed you before.

12:08.240 --> 12:09.880
Glasses here,

12:09.880 --> 12:11.120
dishes here. OK?

12:11.120 --> 12:13.560
CAR HORN BEEPS

12:13.560 --> 12:17.560
Oh, there's my taxi.
Oh, shoot! My backpack.

12:18.640 --> 12:20.320
No clean good.

12:20.320 --> 12:24.320
(GASPS WITH PAIN)

12:24.760 --> 12:28.080
  Adios, Morena! See you at Noel.

12:28.080 --> 12:32.080
   Morena? What's wrong? Morena?

12:32.840 --> 12:34.880
'Dr James Cooper, admitting.'

12:34.880 --> 12:38.880
'Dr James Cooper, admitting.'

12:40.320 --> 12:42.880
&lt; All right,
let's move it over here.

12:42.880 --> 12:44.440
What's the problem?

12:44.440 --> 12:46.920
(MUMBLES DRUNKENLY)

12:46.920 --> 12:47.960
       Name?

12:47.960 --> 12:49.960
Michael Dukakis.

12:49.960 --> 12:50.400
Occupation?

12:50.400 --> 12:51.840
Occupation?
Governor.

12:51.840 --> 12:53.160
Governor of what?

12:53.160 --> 12:55.200
Commonwealth of Massachusetts.

12:55.200 --> 12:58.360
Baloney, that's... What's his name?

12:58.360 --> 13:00.440
I'm what's his name!

13:00.440 --> 13:04.440
Have a seat.

13:06.840 --> 13:10.200
Seven-car demolition derby on
the Mass Pike. This guy's stable.

13:10.200 --> 13:11.400
More wagons behind me.

13:11.400 --> 13:14.000
Ward's full, we'll have
to triage in the hallway.

13:14.000 --> 13:17.000
Clear the walk-ins out of the
ward, get whoever's on call.

13:17.000 --> 13:19.360
Clear the people in the hall.

13:19.360 --> 13:21.360
Elliot? Let's move him over.

13:21.360 --> 13:23.040
You giving something away?

13:23.040 --> 13:24.440
Yeah, free space.

13:24.440 --> 13:28.000
The city's sweeping up bums and
putting them in municipal shelters.

13:28.000 --> 13:29.560
They're all hiding out here.

13:29.560 --> 13:31.000
I'll get the next one!

13:31.000 --> 13:32.240
You don't look so bad.

13:32.240 --> 13:34.960
Minor lacerations,
possible broken clavicle.

13:34.960 --> 13:36.560
Cuts and a broken collarbone.

13:36.560 --> 13:38.440
Massive blood loss and head trauma.

13:38.440 --> 13:42.440
  She's first. This one can wait.

13:43.520 --> 13:47.520
   And this one is beyond help.

13:48.360 --> 13:51.200
Your blood pressure is low
and you're running a fever.

13:51.200 --> 13:53.640
I always get colds
this time of year.

13:53.640 --> 13:56.880
I just came in to St Eligius
avoid the cherry tops.

13:56.880 --> 13:57.920
           You coughing up any blood?

13:57.920 --> 13:59.720
           You coughing up any blood?
Yeah, just a speck or two.

13:59.720 --> 14:01.240
       I'd like to get a chest X-ray.

14:01.240 --> 14:02.440
I'd rather take a nap.

14:02.440 --> 14:03.840
           Well, you can sleep later.

14:03.840 --> 14:05.160
Shh!

14:05.160 --> 14:07.320
Listen to that.

14:07.320 --> 14:08.240
               I don't hear anything.

14:08.240 --> 14:12.080
               I don't hear anything.
I know. Silence.

14:12.080 --> 14:14.840
Do you have any idea
how noisy the world is?

14:14.840 --> 14:18.840
Traffic, sirens, construction,
helicopters, mass transit...

14:20.880 --> 14:23.760
It's a high-decibel
merry-go-round out there.

14:23.760 --> 14:26.040
Sometimes it's like...

14:26.040 --> 14:29.400
Well, it gets in your head,
like bees are inside.

14:29.400 --> 14:32.760
(COUGHS)

14:32.760 --> 14:35.000
Could I brush my teeth?

14:35.000 --> 14:36.640
                                Sure.

14:36.640 --> 14:38.880
I thought bums sleep
through everything?

14:38.880 --> 14:42.080
Yeah, but that ain't sleep,
it's just not moving.

14:42.080 --> 14:46.080
You've got your radar going
constantly, looking for cops

14:46.480 --> 14:50.480
or thieves or some idiot driving
a garbage truck over your legs.

14:51.000 --> 14:55.000
Real sleep, the REM model,
it's only a dream.

14:55.400 --> 14:59.400
                                What?

14:59.760 --> 15:02.440
Forget it.

15:02.440 --> 15:03.920
          Let's get off to Radiology.

15:03.920 --> 15:06.400
When you swore as a kid,
did your mom used to wash

15:06.400 --> 15:10.240
      your mouth out with toothpaste?

15:10.240 --> 15:13.280
          Cardiac needle.

15:13.280 --> 15:15.080
"Oh, for crying out loud, Ehrlich!

15:15.080 --> 15:17.560
"We're not trussing
a Christmas turkey here.

15:17.560 --> 15:20.400
"My granddaughter
ties a better purse string!"

15:20.400 --> 15:22.960
             Yes, sir.

15:22.960 --> 15:24.320
Victor?

15:24.320 --> 15:27.000
What are you doing?

15:27.000 --> 15:29.440
Reminiscing about the good old days.

15:29.440 --> 15:31.440
Aren't you supposed to be in OBGYN?

15:31.440 --> 15:34.560
It's a slow day, thank Yahweh.

15:34.560 --> 15:38.480
You know, all I ever wanted
to be was a surgeon.

15:38.480 --> 15:41.960
Did exercises to strengthen my hands,

15:41.960 --> 15:45.960
practised tying knots in the dark,
I memorised every move Dr Craig made.

15:46.000 --> 15:49.360
I don't have an interest in any
other field. Surgery's my life.

15:49.360 --> 15:50.400
So? &gt;

15:50.400 --> 15:53.360
