to obstetrics and gynaecology.

15:53.360 --> 15:57.360
That's how I felt when I told
Dr Westphall about my medical degree

15:58.120 --> 15:59.800
and he placed me in the pharmacy.

15:59.800 --> 16:02.160
Hold the phone, I'm not a bozo!

16:02.160 --> 16:06.160
What I mean is you can learn,
       no matter where you are.

16:06.240 --> 16:09.480
Yeah. Don't worry,
I've got it all figured out.

16:09.480 --> 16:10.800
Accepting who you are?

16:10.800 --> 16:13.680
No, you see, I spend a week
in the infertility clinic,

16:13.680 --> 16:16.680
mostly counselling.
Then I move right into GYN Oncology,

16:16.680 --> 16:20.400
older women, nothing at stake there.
Another week by the boards.

16:20.400 --> 16:24.400
Meanwhile, I find a medical student,
express an interest in teaching him.

16:24.440 --> 16:26.920
Any hands-on work,
this guy handles. Perfect!

16:26.920 --> 16:28.080
What are you talking about?

16:28.080 --> 16:29.560
What are you talking about?
You see, if this plan works,

16:29.560 --> 16:31.200
I could be the first resident

16:31.200 --> 16:35.120
to go through OBGYN rotation without
ever touching a nubile young woman.

16:35.120 --> 16:36.880
You're sick, Victor.

16:36.880 --> 16:40.880
Fantastic, Boomer. If all else fails,
I get sick and skip the whole thing!

16:43.880 --> 16:47.880
             Ah, yeah!

16:48.320 --> 16:52.000
I didn't think the board would fund
